The city has a modern container-port to handle imports and exports.
 The port is part of the 21st Century Maritime Silk Road that runs from the Chinese coast via the Suez Canal to the Mediterranean,
  there to the Upper Adriatic region of Trieste with its rail connections to Central and Eastern Europe.
The main airport is Port Sudan New International Airport. 
There is now a tarred road linking Port Sudan to Khartoum via Atbara. 
Port Sudan also has a rail link with Khartoum. 
There is also an international ferry from Jeddah